benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: PUT /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/cbaRebalancing - Rebalance account CBA

covered: PUT Valid Request: Multiple scenarios cover successful rebalancing with required and optional headers (TC01-TC07).
Non-Existing Resource / Invalid Account ID: Tests TC08 and TC09 cover non-existent and invalid account ID format errors.
Concurrency Handling: TC18 and TC21 cover high concurrency and parallel requests with consistent CBA.
Unsupported HTTP method: TC22 ensures 405 when using GET on the endpoint.
Header validation and security: TC10-TC12, TC15, TC24-TC26 test missing/empty/malicious headers and extra headers.
Error handling / resilience: TC13 (network retry), TC14 (service unavailable).
Boundary/Edge cases: TC16 (very large accountId), TC17 (empty database).
Performance tests: TC20, TC21 measure response time under load.
Regression: TC19 checks previously fixed bug.
Data/state variations: TC04-TC07 cover various initial CBA states and transactions.
gaps: Partial Update behavior not explicitly tested for PUT (PUT implies full update; gap remains for validating rejection of partial fields).
Authorization/Authentication failure scenarios (e.g., 401/403 with invalid/expired tokens) are not covered.
Rate limiting / throttling scenarios are not tested.
Caching headers (ETag/Cache-Control) and related caching behavior are not tested.
500 Internal Server Error scenarios are not explicitly tested (only 503).
Edge-case security tests beyond header-level (e.g., content-type mismatches, header encoding) are not covered.
recommendations: Add tests for unauthorized access: 401/403 when the token is invalid or expired.
Introduce rate limiting tests to ensure proper throttling and retry behavior under load.
Add caching validation tests (ETag/Cache-Control) for PUT /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/cbaRebalancing.
Add tests for 500 Internal Server Error scenarios and database failures.
Clarify and include explicit Partial Update tests or explain PUT semantics; ensure tests verify rejection of partial updates if applicable.
Consider additional security tests around other headers and input integrity.
Expand coverage for performance by more varied load patterns and longer durations.
